# Grow Your Twitter Account Faster w/ “Follow Intent” Links

Topics: Growth Hacks, Social Media Marketing

Most people have links to their social media accounts all over the place:

- Website navbars, footers, blog posts
- Other social media accounts
- Linktrees
- etc.

And if you do, great — but you’re missing out on some *easy wins.*

Because you’re probably linking like this: [https://twitter.com/dvnschmchr](https://twitter.com/dvnschmchr)

👇 Do this instead 👇

Instead of linking directly to your Twitter account URL..

Use a “follow intent link” so the user gets **automatically prompted to follow** your account when the page loads!

![https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*UHFdzS0CmWI6cOl5_VdD6Q.png](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*UHFdzS0CmWI6cOl5_VdD6Q.png)

# **How to make a Twitter “Follow Intent Link”**

All you have to do to get this auto “follow me” pop-up on page load is to make a simple adjustment to the URL.

Before your twitter handle, add:`intent/follow?screen_name=`

So instead of this:

[https://twitter.com/dvnschmchr](https://twitter.com/dvnschmchr)

**Do this:**

[https://twitter.com/**intent/follow?screen_name=**dvnschmchr](https://twitter.com/intent/follow?screen_name=dvnschmchr)

☝ And of course, always use a [serp.ly](http://serp.ly/) link so you have better tracking on how effective your marketing is!

